title: For Sale:  Remington 700 .223 Rem- B&C Timney Simmons Dednutz Harris
postcontent:
Decided to sell my Remington 700 .223 rifle.  Don't really want to sell it, but I'm not using it nearly as much as I thought I would, and can use the money toward other things.  I bought this gun brand new last fall, and have fired exactly 40 rounds through it in one range session.  I have a bunch of loading supplies, reloading tools, ect available for purchase separately either with the gun or after the gun sells.

The gun is set up as follows:

-Remington 700 .223 Rem.  BDL setup (hinged floorplate), matte finished metal.  26" bull barrel, 1-12" twist rate 

-Timney 510 trigger.  Adjustable from 1.5lb to 4lb.  This specific trigger was custom tuned by Timney, so its a little bit nicer than one you'd get directly out of the package.

-Bell & Carlson M40 stock.  Specific model number is 1000-23.  It is grey with black webbing.  This stock has an aluminum bedding block.

-Simmons Whitetail Classic 6.5-20x50 scope.  Obviously not a top-of-the-line scope, but it is one of the most popular scopes, regardless of price, on Midway, and I think its a great "bang for the buck".  I'm not a scope snob, and I think this scope would be more than adequate for the range of a .223

-DNZ Dednutz one piece scope mount.  A real slick setup that combines the bases and rings in one setup, so the rings are guaranteed to be straight and parallel, minimizing scope movement and all but eliminating any risk of scope damage.

-Score High Benchrest Single Shot follower.  This makes benchrest work much more convenient, just drop the cartridge in the action and close the bolt, no fumbling around if you want to load one shell at a time.  Installs and removes in seconds.

-Tactical Component Mfg Mag-Xtender.  This replaces the OEM floorplate (which is included) and increases the ammunition capacity from 5 rounds to 9 rounds.  Easily interchangeable with the OEM floorplate.

-Hornady stock pack.  It is left handed, so if you don’t want/need it I can knock $30 off the price.

-Butler Creek Flip-Up scope cap covers

title: For Sale:  1942 Izhevsk Mosin Nagant PU Sniper ( not Finnish or Finn )
location: Hanover, Henrico, Hopewell etc., Richmond, Virginia
postcontent:
Collectors, 

I have decided to part with one of my Mosin Nagant PU snipers.

This is not a reproduction or one of the CAI (Century) put togethers.

If you know about Mosin PU sniper rifles you may also know that 1942 is a rare and very difficult to find production year (because of it being a transitional year from PE and PEM sniper production) as PU sniper production didn't start until later in that year.

This rifle is all stamped matching with the letter prefix's although the magazine floorplate has been lined out and renumbered to match.

It is a wartime issue rifle and unlike many others this PU rifle may have a history behind it.

The scope is numbers matching to the mount and rifles barrel shank.

Bore and crown are in good condition with no counter-bore.

More pic.s are available to seriously interested parties.

So if you want an good example of a WW2 PU sniper rifle that few people can say they own, this one may be for you.

I would like $800 for this very collectable and shootable rifle and I am looking for a FTF sale in the Richmond, Virginia (Tri-Cities) area but may travel a short distance to help with the sale.

Last picture is of this rifle in a more natural setting.
